1.title: Venus Guy Trap
1.plot: Beautiful nursing student Taiana Matheny falls for rising rap star Terry Sellers-but their romantic getaway turns murderous crime spree with Taiana as their irresistible bait.

2.title: More Than a Babysitter
2.plot: When pregnant suburban mom Tina Young becomes addicted to heroin, she ditches her family for her new lover, ex-con drug dealer, Larry Tooley. When the unlikely pair is short on cash, they target a family Tina used to babysit for, with deadly results.

3.title: Mommy's Little Helpers
3.plot: Beautiful matriarch Laura Hernandez is used to getting her way. When her husband, Alberto Macias, faces financial trouble, Laura decides he's worth more dead than alive. Laura pulls out all the stops and manipulates her children into a deadly plot.

4.title: Straight Through the Heartland
4.plot: Indiana teen Wendy Lewis gets more than she bargained for when she takes a babysitting job for engineer Wayne Gulley as an affair leads to a deadly crime spree taking decades to solve.

5.title: A Recipe for Disaster
5.plot: Criminal lovebirds Roger Gillett and Lisa Chamberlin plan a quiet trip out of town to keep police off their trail. But when they show up at Roger's cousin's home, things quickly spiral out of control leading authorities to a barn filled with horrors.

6.title: Freedom Quest
6.plot: Beautiful, charismatic tattoo aficionado Melanie Ray has a dark past and no desire to go back to prison on a parole violation-when she meets up with childhood friend Chandler Clark sparks fly and the pair begins a love affair that will end in murder.

7.title: The Dark Krystal
7.plot: Troubled teen Krystal Hall teams up with meth maniac Patrick Connelly and the pair goes on a murderous rampage that leads to a high speed chase and showdown in the swamps of Florida.

9.title: A Mother's Worst NIghtmare
9.plot: When off-the-wagon addict Casey Ledbetter falls for compulsive con-woman Jo, the combustible couple gets wrapped up in a series of scams for which their only escape is murder-but things escalate as the lovers turn on friends and become serial killers.

10.title: Dirty Double Cross
10.plot: Ice queen Alesia Warrior plots with her lover, Darell Rodgers to kill her husband for his insurance money-but when Darell accidentally paralyzes Alesia in the shooting, she's forced to up the ante to confuse police to keep them off the couple's trail.

11.title: No Easy Road
11.plot: When young traveler Bo McNeely meets trucker C.J. Harvey, he gets more than just a ride when C.J. takes Bo home to meet the entire drug-fueled Harvey clan, who team up to torture and kill Bo before getting in a massive armed standoff with police.

12.title: The Cougar and Her Cub
12.plot: Mother and daughter grifters, Sherrie and Dianne Dicus team up with 19-year-old Steven Wesolek, sharing love and drugs in the hot Florida swamplands as the trio try to escape their troubled pasts and set off on a violent and deadly path to freedom.

13.title: True Bromance
13.plot: Bored and rich, Alabama teen Nathan Lee partners with local loafer Troy Smiley to hunt the most dangerous game-humans! But when the pair kills a young friend, Blake Stone, they turn the tables and convince police that Blake's step-mom is the murderer.

14.title: Prey for Me
14.plot: Suburban housewife Dawn Fowler tires of her crippled husband, Richard-so with made-up tales of Richard's 'abuse', Dawn hatches a plan to seduce a youth pastor, Robert Heydman, and convince him to kill her husband and free her from his reign of terror.

1.title: The Perfect Couple
1.plot: When a teenage girl disappears in a small Canadian town, police assume she's a runaway. But when her body shows up sexually assaulted and dismembered and another young girl is missing, police fear they have a predator on the loose. Tips from the community lead the police to the door of a junior accountant. But he doesn't fit the profile of a sexually sadistic killer, he's attractive and charming and recently married to a beautiful woman from a good family. They are the all-Canadian couple.

2.title: Minivan Murders
2.plot: Wicked Attraction looks at the case of James Daveggio and Michelle Michaud who used a minivan to abduct and assault several young women in Southern California.

3.title: Madness of Two
3.plot: Wicked Attraction looks at the case of Elizabeth Haysom who convinced her 18-year-old boyfriend Jens Söring to kill her retired parents.

4.title: Evil in the Desert
4.plot: Wicked Attraction examines the 'Toy Box Murders' of David Parker Ray and Cindy Hendy who kidnapped and sexually assaulted a series of young women in Truth or Consequences, New Mexico.

5.title: Blood Brothers
5.plot: Wicked Attraction examines the case of Charles Ng and Leonard Lake who were responsible for a series of rapes and murders in central California.

6.title: Twisted Twosome
6.plot: Wicked Attraction looks at the case of Gerald and Charlene Gallego who abduct and kill a series of teenagers in Sacramento, California.

7.title: Mother Knows Best
7.plot: Wicked Attraction looks at the mother and son con artist team of Sante and Kenny Kimes who are linked to robbery, fraud, and two murders.

8.title: Kidnapped
8.plot: Wicked Attraction examines the kidnapping of Colleen Stan who was held as a sex slave for seven years by Cameron and Janice Hooker.

9.title: Our Little Secret
9.plot: Wicked Attraction examines the case of Gwendolyn Graham and Cathy Wood who may have smothered five elderly women while working as nurse's aides in Grand Rapids, Michigan.

10.title: Hearts of Darkness
10.plot: Wicked Attraction looks at the case of Alvin Neelley and his troubled teenage wife Judith who were sentenced for the torture and murders of two young women.

11.title: Murder at Twilight
11.plot: Wicked Attraction examines the case of Ray and Faye Copeland an elderly couple who were behind a cattle scheme in Nebraska that led to the murder of five drifters.

12.title: Driven by Desire
12.plot: Wicked Attraction looks at spree killer Alton Coleman and his accomplice Debra Brown who were response for the rape of murder of eight women in the Midwest.

13.title: Death on the Sunset Strip
13.plot: Wicked Attraction looks at the case of the "Sunset Strip Killers" in which Douglas Clark and Carol M. Bundy murdered several young prostitutes and runaways in Los Angeles, California.

1.title: The Two Bears
1.plot: Wicked Attraction examines the case of counter-culture serial killers Michael Bear Carson and Suzan Carson who kill three people in the San Francisco Bay Area believing themselves to be Islamic witch-hunters.

2.title: The Golden Years
2.plot: Wicked Attraction examines the "Black Widow Murders" of Helen Golay and Olga Rutterschmidt two elderly women who killed homeless men for insurance money.

3.title: The Folsom Wolf
3.plot: Wicked Attraction examines the case of ex-con James Gregory Marlow and Cynthia Coffman who set out on a cross country spree of rape, torture, and murder.

4.title: A Mother's Love
4.plot: Wicked Attractions looks at the case of Theresa Knorr who brutally murder two of her own children while using her other children to help facilitate and cover-up the crime.

5.title: Payback
5.plot: Wicked Attraction looks at the case of David Anderson and Alex Baranyi who are responsible for a quadruple homicide known as the Bellevue Massacre.

6.title: Toolbox Killers
6.plot: Wicked Attraction examines the case of Lawrence Bittaker and Roy Norris who kidnapped, tortured, and murdered five teenage girls in California.

7.title: Opportunity Knocks
7.plot: Wicked Attraction examines the case of Alicia Woodward and John Esposito two teenage lovers who go on a cross-country spree of robbery and murder targeting elderly men and women.

8.title: My Girl
8.plot: Wicked Attraction examines the case of Michelle Hetzel and her husband Brandon Bloss who brutally stab and kill Michelle's lesbian lover Devon Guzman.

9.title: Consumed by Envy
9.plot: Wicked Attraction examines the case of Jacqueline Williams and Fedell Caffey murdered an entire family in order to steal their unborn baby.

10.title: No Remorse
10.plot: 18-year-old Sarah Emondson and Ben Barras are a violent couple that travel across the country, killing anyone who comes near their path. Their trail goes cold for nearly a year, until a major break in the case arises.

11.title: Single White Male
11.plot: Wicked Attraction examines the case of Patrick Selepak and Samantha Bachynski who murder a couple and their unborn baby after a long string of robberies.

12.title: Picture Perfect
12.plot: Wicked Attraction examines the case of navy cadet Diane Zamora and her boyfriend David Graham who murder one of her romantic rivals.

13.title: Dead or Alive
13.plot: Wicked Attraction looks at the case of ex-con Joshua Maxwell and former cheerleader Tessie McFarland who murder an Indiana mechanic and then go on a cross-country crime spree.

1.title: Built for Murder
1.plot: Wicked Attractions looks at the case of bodybuilder Craig Titus and fitness model Kelly Ryan who are responsible for the murder of their assistant Melissa James.

2.title: Home Sweet Home
2.plot: Wicked Attraction examines the case of Michelle and David Knotek lure guests to their Washington boardinghouse in order to murder them.

3.title: Evil in the Blood
3.plot: Wicked Attraction examines the case of Ricky Gray and Ray Dandridge who were responsible for a spree of family murders in Richmond Virginia.

4.title: Superstar
4.plot: Wicked Attraction looks at the case of former boxer Jeremy Brooks and Coty Rodriguez who commit three murders in three different states.

5.title: Beyond the Wire
5.plot: Wicked Attraction looks at the case of Carolyn King and Bradley Martin who kill a Pennsylvania florist and later kidnap and murder a woman in North Dakota.

6.title: Innocence Lost
6.plot: Wicked Attraction looks at the case of Michael Thornton who uses his young protégé Janeen Snyder to kidnap and murder two teen girls.

7.title: Calm Before the Storm
7.plot: Wicked Attraction looks at the case of Skylar Deleon and his wife Jennifer Henderson who kill a California couple and steal their yacht.

8.title: Shoot to Thrill
8.plot: Wicked Attraction looks at the case of Dale Hausner and Sam Dieteman two serial shooters who targeted the streets of Phoenix, Arizona.

9.title: Dial 123
9.plot: Wicked Attraction examines the case of Kelly Gissendaner and her lover Gregory Owen who conspire to murder Kelly's husband Doug.

10.title: Live Free or Die
10.plot: Wicked Attraction examines the case of Nicole Kasinskas who kills her mother Jeanne Dominico when she refuses to let her move in with her boyfriend Billy Sullivan.

11.title: Deadly Disciple
11.plot: Wicked Attraction examines the case of the "Children of Thunder" Justin and Glenn Helzer who murder five people in Northern California in order to raise money for their battle with Satan.

12.title: Crossing the Line
12.plot: Wicked Attraction examines the case of ex-con Darnell Smith and his girlfriend and former prison guard Tina Leja who murder and dismember a man in Wisconsin.

13.title: A Lover's Betrayal
13.plot: Wicked Attraction examines the case of Michael Dally who secret life and affair with Diana Haun led to the murder Michael's wife Sherri Dally.

1.title: Till Death Us Do Part
1.plot: After 16 years of violent abuse Deborah Brown and her children have decided to flee from her husband Steven Brown. They think they'll be safe living with Deborah's brother Don in a different state. Then one night Steven arrives to exact his revenge, and Deborah endures a night of sheer terror.

2.title: 57 Seconds
2.plot: The ordeal of Lisa Fotopoulos, who survived a gunshot to the head in a botched murder-for-hire scheme.

3.title: Dante's Inferno
3.plot: Masked robbers burst into a Eustis, FL bachelor party and open fire on the guests. Two men are killed and another is seriously injured after being shot ten times. The mastermind of the robbery is drug dealer Donte Hall. He enlisted the help of his stripper girlfriend Angel Glenn, who was working the party, and his identical twin brother Dante. Now police must find them before they kill again.

4.title: Bad Fortune
4.plot: In the spring of 2005, prominent Vietnamese fortune teller Ha Smith and her daughter Anita Vo are found brutally stabbed to death inside their Orange County, CA home. In a puzzling twist, their killer has also poured white paint over their bodies. As detectives consider the possibility of a ritual killing, new purchases are being made on Ha Smith's credit cards. The money trail leads police to a North Carolina woman who also happens to be a client of Ha Smith.

5.title: Road to Nowhere
5.plot: In the fall of 2004, police officers rescue Jennifer Hitchcock from the Wisconsin hotel room where her abusive and obsessive boyfriend, Maurice Mason, has been holding her. But Mason refuses to let her go. He recruits his nephew Bennie Frier as an accomplice and follows Jennifer to Nebraska, where he intends to get her back - no matter what. Mason tracks down his one time lover, savagely beats her, and kidnaps her. He and Frier then begin the trip back to Wisconsin. It's a trip that will find one man bound and left for dead in the wilderness, a cab driver gunned down,...

6.title: See No Evil
6.plot: In January of 2000 Danielle Simpson, his wife Jennifer, and a 13-year-old friend decide to rob the home of their elderly neighbor, 84-year-old widow Geraldine Davidson. They break in while she's out, but are startled when the retired school teacher returns home while they are still in her house. The trio kidnaps the elderly woman, bind her with duct tape, and force her into the trunk of her own car. They then drive around the town of Palestine, TX, stopping to show her off to friends along the way. When Danielle Simpson's younger brother Lionel joins them, he ...

7.title: Good Deeds Punished
7.plot: In July of 2005, elderly couple Carol and Reggie Sumner go missing from their Jacksonville, FL home. A few days later, their abandoned car turns up about an hour away from home. Then someone starts withdrawing cash from their bank accounts at ATM's in Charleston, SC, where they used to live. Investigators follow the paper trail right to Michael Jackson and Tiffany Cole. The young couple has a connection to the Sumner's. Tiffany Cole used to be their neighbor. Jackson and Cole, along with friends Alan Wade and Bruce Nixon, have committed an unspeakable crime.

8.title: The Golden Buddha
8.plot: On the night of August 9, 1991, two men break into the Buddhist temple on the outskirts of Phoenix, AZ and murder all 9 people inside. The motive appears to be robbery. Based on a tip, a special task force quickly arrests four Tucson, AZ men and charges them with the murders. But ballistics tests on a confiscated .22 rifle connect the murders to two teenagers - Jonathan Doody and Alessandro "Alex" Garcia. While being questioned, Garcia admits he and Doody are the real killers.

9.title: Deadly Rival
9.plot: Wicked Attraction examines the case of California's Michael Simons and his girlfriend Katie Belflower who conspired together to murder Michael's seventeen year-old estranged wife Jenna Nannetti. They had hoped to collect on a large insurance policy taken out of Jenna's life.

10.title: Sex, Lies, and Bloody Goodbyes
10.plot: Catherina Voss is obsessed by sex, men, and spending money she hasn't got. In April 2007 she decides the quickest way to a fast buck is to hire a hit man to kill her latest husband, Navy Ensign Cory Voss. As Catherina waits excitedly for the life insurance check to arrive Police begin to delve into her background, and discover her latest lover, Michael Draven, tells as many lies as she does - claiming he's a successful movie producer when in fact he's hardly worked a day in his life.

11.title: The Jaycee Dugard Story
11.plot: The case of Jaycee Lee Dugard who was abducted at age eleven from South Lake Tahoe, California. She is kept as a slave for eighteen years by Phillip Craig Garrido and his wife Nancy.

12.title: Lesbians and the Little Man
12.plot: Wicked Attraction examines the robbery and stoning death of pool shark and little person Donald Fish in Roseburg, Oregon. He was last seen leaving a bar with the lesbian couple of Tracy Lee Poirier and Tamara Marie Upton. The couple are arrested in a stolen car and are later found guilty of murder. Tracy eventually seduces a guard and manages to escape.

13.title: Rough Diamond
13.plot: Two lovers are prepared to go to any lengths to pay for their next drug fix which is costing over $600 a day. They decide robbing jewelry stores is the best way to get fast cash. They start their robbing spree in the holiday season of 2004, and the bodies soon start to mount.

1.title: No Sharing Allowed
1.plot: After murdering a pornographer preying on underage girls, a pair of teenage lesbian lovers hit the road with their family in a 'Thelma and Louise' style escape from the police.

2.title: Houseguests from Hell
2.plot: An elderly couple gets more than they bargained for when their house guests from hell wreak havoc, eventually teaming up with another pair of murderers to break out of jail and lead authorities on a nationwide manhunt.

3.title: A Slice of Murder
3.plot: A homicidal manager with a pizza chain seeks revenge by unleashing a reign of terror and murder accompanied by his twisted new girlfriend who is happy to entice fresh victims.

4.title: Fascination with Death
4.plot: An unlikely brotherhood is forged between two homicidal men with psychotic fantasies of murder, maiming and cannibalism.

5.title: Lust for Life
5.plot: A dapper con-man with expensive taste and an appetite for the finer things in life goes to explosive lengths to play his game.

6.title: Death Ride
6.plot: Two mentally unhinged ex-military men team up for a deadly crime spree as their obsession with living life on the edge grows out of control.

7.title: The Power of Love
7.plot: Former childhood sweethearts Jason and Missy plan to kill Missy's elderly lover and inherit millions, but their plan quickly spirals out of control as Missy tries to manipulate the police.

8.title: The Body Shifters
8.plot: Love struck teens discover committing murder is easy - but getting rid of the body can prove a real problem...

9.title: Rebels with a Deadly Cause
9.plot: A couple of vicious lovers from rival SoCal gangs randomly commit a string of robberies, torture and murders causing sheer terror throughout the San Gabriel Valley.

10.title: Weapon of Mass Seduction
10.plot: An-ex hooker and a smooth-talking gigolo team up to lure a high end car dealership owner into pure temptation...instead, it leads to nothing but a brutal murder.

11.title: Dressed to Kill
11.plot: Bored with a dull life under the thumb of her over-protective parents, Leslie Ballard discovers a fast life of sex and passion with a man more than 20 years her senior. Left short in her rich father's will, an heiress finds a million reasons to get even.

12.title: Love Me Tenderizer
12.plot: Jealousy knows no limits as sadistic psycho Mike Murdaugh and his twisted lover Becky Rohrs brutally torment Becky's admirers.

13.title: A Rose Amongst Thorns
13.plot: Rose Goggins is engaged to 25 year-old Robert Beersdorf. Rose is determined to give her son the family she never had, but her soon to be in-laws aren't exactly welcoming her into the family. While Robert is away at basic training camp, he asks Rose to move in with his parents, Steven and Sylvia. For Rose, the experience becomes a real life house of horror.

14.title: Wheels of Steel
14.plot: Texan Sandra Stotler, 50, son, Adam Stotler, 17, and his friend Jeremy Richardson, 18, go missing in 2001. A car chase leads to the drivers of Stotler's red convertible. Sandra's white SUV is also gone. Her absent son and friend are immediately suspected. However, a cold-blooded twist reveals the true victims, thieves, and shocking plot to "steal some wheels."

imdb.title: Wicked Attraction
plot: Examines cases where perverse desires push real people to commit murder.::Toby Padilla
